  "text": "Some cases of alkaptonuria are diagnosed in infancy due to darkening of urine when exposed to air. However, clinical symptoms first appear in adulthood. The most prominent symptoms relate to joint and connective tissue involvement; significant cardiac disease and urolithiasis may be detected in the later years [CITATION_1] .",
